# ── LOCAL DEV ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy to .env.local. With this set, the browser calls Gemini directly (the key
# stays on your machine). Get a free key: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=

# ── DEPLOYED (Vercel) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Do NOT set VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY in production — a VITE_ var is baked into the
# public bundle and anyone could read it. Instead, in the Vercel dashboard set:
#
#     GEMINI_API_KEY = <your key>      (Settings → Environment Variables)
#
# The deployed browser then calls /api/gemini (the serverless proxy), which holds
# the key server-side. Nothing secret ever reaches the browser.
